<h1>From Horatio Gates</h1>

<div class="docbody">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft"><span class="hi-small-caps" style="font-variant: small-caps;">Sir</span></td>
		<td class="salutationRight">Hillsborough 20th. Octr. 1780.</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>I wrote Your Excellency the 18th. which was sent from hence By Express, on the Evening of that Day, and would proceed to Taylors Ferry, as Mr. Cooper the Stationed Express at Harrisbourg, was, at the Same Time on his Way to this place; the Latter arrived here Yesterday about One oClock A.M. and brought me Your Excellencys Letter of the 15th. Inst. This Letter, came in Time, which was not the Case with several Others written before, from you, as I observe, some of them were, from a week to Twelve Days in coming to this place. The following is the State of the correspondence since the 1st. of Sepr. 1780.</p>
<table class="bodytext" style="margin-left: 4em;">
<tr>
	      <td colspan="3">Genl. Gates</td>
	      <td colspan="2">Govr. Jefferson</td>
	    </tr>
<tr>
	      <td>Sepr.</td>
	      <td style="text-align: right;">5</td>
	      <td></td>
	      <td>Sepr.</td>
	      <td style="text-align: right;">3</td>
	    </tr>
